+WoundingWind First off, you seem to be working a little too hard to prove 
this theory even though there are way too many holes. Going off what 
Maijatus98 said; Elsa and Anna were well into their mid- and late-teens. 
This would suggest that the Queen is at least in her 30's already (31 at 
least if she had married and had Elsa at 13, which was the common marrying 
age and the average age to start puberty). Even if she had Tarzan some 
30-odd years later, this would put her well into her 60's, not 50's, which 
then it would be basically be impossible, if anything slimmer than a 1 in a 
billion!
Now, another thing. Their clothes. Being very active in history and 
fashion, I know very well that the clothes seen on Tarzan's parents are in 
fact from England during the Victorian era (1837-1901), as the King and 
Queen's clothes are from the early 19th century (1800-40) in Norway. Though 
yes the two timelines clash, it's very late in the time Frozen takes place 
verses very early in Queen Victoria's reign. Aside from that, if the King 
and Queen of Arendelle visited England, they wouldn't have changed 
wardrobes when they returned to their ship. Nor would they have just 
randomly changed ships if they were to return home on the same ship in two 
weeks.
Another thing on appearance, the parents in either movie are polar opposite 
in the looks department. While Tarzan's father looks very rugged with a 
facial hairstyle of the Victorian era, blue eyes, and brown hair, the King 
is more well kept, a thin mustache, green-ish eyes, and ginger hair. And 
Tarzan's mother is mature-looking with curly red hair and brown eyes while 
the Queen appears younger, is brunette, and possesses blue eyes.
Also, as stated before, the ship in Tarzan was on fire when it drowned 
while the Frozen ship did just sink, no flames. I remember this clearly as 
I have done a theater performance based off "Do You Want to Build a 
Snowman" which included this particular scene.
Next, how and why would the King and Queen be in Africa is they're only to 
be gone for two weeks? It would make perfect since if they're attending a 
royal wedding in Germany as that's only a few days trip by ship. They would 
have a little over a week to attend the wedding, spend time in Corona, have 
dinner with Rapunzel and her family, then sail back to Arendelle. It would 
be very difficult for their ship to sail off course all they way to Africa. 
Maybe to Britain, yes, but to Africa? That's near impossible with islands 
in your way if the ship got set on course to the Atlantic Ocean.
Last thing, remember that picture of Tarzan's parents and him as a baby? 
Remember the painting in the castle of Arendelle? If the King and Queen had 
cameras, why would there be a painting of the two in the castle rather than 
photo?

searched it on the internet and it said that it has been confirmed), Their 
parents couldn't really be in their 20's. If they had kids at a very young 
age, they could be in their 30's, but I doubt their mother was under 15 
when she had her second child. Besides, we need more than 30 years for the 
time. Yes, technology develops really fast now, but it didn't develop as 
fast back then. Even if it would be possible with the developing, There was 
still almost a 100 year gap between the times the movies were set. And the 
difference is not only in the ships and stuff like that, it's also the 
clothing and stuff they have. The style of clothing is different in the 
movies, and I think it would be weird if the parents suddenly had new, more 
modern clothes after being on a ship for so long that everythng had changed 
dramatically.
Also, the movie shows it pretty clearly that in Tarzan the ship sinked 
while it was on fire, but in Frozen the ship just sinks.
And yeah, people have survived for a long time at sea, but like 30 years? I 
don't think so. You said it yourself, Jesus Vidana was at sea for 9 months, 
and that was in 2005. This was a long time ago which means his boat was way 
better than the ships in Frozen and Tarzan.
Also, how would you explain the parents' looks? They look nothing alike to 
begin with, and if it really was possible for them to survive all of this 
and everything to change so quickly and for them to be in their 50's and 
still have a baby (which by the way, is not very easy, most women get their 
menopause at around 45 to 50, and fertility goes down a lot after like 35 
to 40 soo, having a baby at that age, well, possible, but not very easy) 
they couldn't look that young in Tarzan. They would have grey hair and the 
father would most likely be balding.

long periods of time at sea...The Longest being done by Jesús Vidaña in 
2005. He was at Sea for 9 Months !!!  And Tho there was fire .. Your still 
on water which can smother the flames at any time if the hull was breached. 
And also keep in mind .... Women can bare children well into their 50's and 
when Ana and Elsa's parents left... they were very young themselves... 
So... Let's create a time line.... If they (the parents) were in their 20's 
when they left and they didn't have Tarzan till they were in there Early

could have changed drastically !!! Ex: 30 years ago .... were there Smart 
Phones? Email ? Public Internet usage ? Hybrid Cars ? Flat Screen TV's? Blu

)....Breaking was still the big dance craze, Back to the Future was a
